        "text": "Hello!\nI don’t know which channel is suited for my question but I just wanted to understand one small thing about `abline` function. I was a little tired using it recently, so easily confused by meaning of `a` and `b` parameters. I wonder if it’s cultural\/tradition difference but I am so used from school to linear function in 2D being expressed as: `y = ax + b` , that how `abline` defines it the other way round made me surprised.\nSo, why really in `abline`  is `a` an *intercept* and `b` a *slope*?",
